sp.p:
Yet thou art brave: Oh Heaven what shall I do to pay the Debt of Gratitude I owe thee; what a forlorn and miserable Wretch had I been but for thee! Oh I am lost! What Beauty, Riches or the Gloss of Honour, with all th' allurements never could subdue, is conquer'd by this great, this generous Action: My Heart is melting, and a new strange passion fills all my bosom, that firm resolute will, that stood unshock'd to the deserts of Chrisostome, is wholly Captive to the brave Ambrosio. In vain is Art or Obstinacy now.
In vain does weakned Force resist the stronger;
The Fort's o're-pow'r'd, and can hold ou • no longer. Exit.

Aw— nay if thou flagg'st to thy old course I hate thee: come I'll refresh thy Genius with a scrap of Poetry I lately met with in an honest Satyr, that suits exactly with the present Theme.




At fourteen Years young Females are contriving Tricks to tempt ye,

At sixteen Years come on and woo, and take of Kisses plenty;

At eighteen Years full grown and ripe, they're ready to content ye;

At nineteen sly and mischievous, but the Devil at one and twenty.

There, there's a Poetical touch now to inspire thee; come, prithee go on now.

